S T A T E O F R H O D E I S L A N D
IN GENERAL ASSEMBLY
JANUARY SESSION, A.D. 2025
____________
A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL OFFENSES -- WEAPONS
Introduced By: Representatives Hull, and Casey
Date Introduced: March 07, 2025
Referred To: House Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Sections 11-47-9.1 and 11-47-35.1 of the General Laws in Chapter 11-47
2 entitled "Weapons" are hereby amended to read as follows:
3 11-47-9.1. Additional exemptions.
4 The provisions of §§ 11-47-8 and 11-47-11 shall not apply to members of the state police,
5 members of city or town police forces, officers or employees of the United States authorized by
6 law to carry a concealed firearm, and members of the Rhode Island airport police department.
7 Persons exempted by the provisions of this section from the provisions of § 11-47-8 shall have the
8 right to carry concealed firearms everywhere within this state; provided, that this shall not be
9 construed as giving the right to carry concealed firearms to a person transporting firearms as
10 merchandise or as household or business goods.
11 11-47-35.1. Persons exempt from § 11-47-35.
12 The provisions of § 11-47-35 shall not apply to full-time members of the state police, full-
13 time members of the state marshal’s office, full-time members of city or town police departments,
14 officers or employees of the United States authorized by law to carry a concealed firearm, or state
15 marshals or correctional officers or persons licensed under § 11-47-11.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
